<subSubSection id="7B8E65470111FF9BFF6ECF499F74C50D" pageId="1" pageNumber="215" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="332B36CC0111FF9BFF6ECF499F74C50D" blockId="1.[136,1452,1172,2063]" pageId="1" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis id="01E0EADE0111FF9BFF6ECF499C42C655" bold="true" box="[189,256,1352,1378]" pageId="1" pageNumber="215">Notes</emphasis>
:—According to 
<bibRefCitation id="57054B3D0111FF9BFE10CF499FB3C655" author="Hertel, H. &amp; Schreiber, A." box="[451,753,1352,1378]" pageId="1" pageNumber="215" pagination="81 - 512" refId="ref3170" refString="Hertel, H. &amp; Schreiber, A. (1988) Die Botanische Staatssammlung Munchen 1813 - 1988 (Eine Ubersicht uber die Sammlungsbestande). Mitteilungen der Botanischen Staatssammlung Munchen 26: 81 - 512. Available from: http: // indexcoll. botanischestaatssammlung. de / (accessed 6 April 2021)" type="journal article" year="1988">Hertel &amp; Schreiber (1988)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="57054B3D0111FF9BFCFFCF499EA9C655" author="Goerdten, U." box="[812,1003,1352,1378]" pageId="1" pageNumber="215" refId="ref3298" refString="Goerdten, U. (2021) Carl Fraas. In: Wikipedia, Die freie Enzyklopadie. Version: 13 May 2021. Available from: https: // de. wikipedia. org / w / index. php? title = Carl _ Fraas &amp; oldid = 211922493 (accessed 28 May 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Goerdten (2021)</bibRefCitation>
, at least parts of Fraas’s herbarium are said to have survived in J.G. Zuccarini’s herbarium (now M, accessed 1849) or in the Herbarium of the Veterinary Faculty of the University of Munich (accessed 1929). Original material of 
<taxonomicName id="F4944D4F0111FF9BFC00CF909915C69D" authorityName="Fraas" authorityYear="1845" box="[979,1111,1424,1451]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Verbascum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="215" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="limnense">
<emphasis id="01E0EADE0111FF9BFC00CF909EA6C69D" box="[979,996,1425,1450]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="215">V</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="01E0EADE0111FF9BFC20CF919915C69D" box="[1011,1111,1424,1450]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="215">limnense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, could not be traced in Munich. Original material of Fraas’s taxon was kept in Spruner’s collection in B seen by 
<bibRefCitation id="57054B3D0111FF9BFB55CFB59837C6F9" author="Murbeck, S. S." box="[1158,1397,1460,1486]" pageId="1" pageNumber="215" refId="ref3647" refString="Murbeck, S. S. (1933) Monographie der Gattung Verbascum. H. Ohlsson, Lund, 630 pp." type="book" year="1933">Murbeck (1933: 408)</bibRefCitation>
who clarified its synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="F4944D4F0111FF9BFE1BCFD99F1FC6C5" authorityName="Zuccarini" authorityYear="1837" box="[456,605,1496,1522]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Celsia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="215" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tomentosa">
<emphasis id="01E0EADE0111FF9BFE1BCFD99F1FC6C5" box="[456,605,1496,1522]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="215">C. tomentosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Unfortunately, this material has most likely been destroyed during World War II (R. Vogt, pers. comm.). Since no original material of the name 
<taxonomicName id="F4944D4F0111FF9BFC5FCFFC9949C521" authorityName="Fraas" authorityYear="1845" box="[908,1035,1532,1558]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Verbascum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="1" pageNumber="215" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="limnense">
<emphasis id="01E0EADE0111FF9BFC5FCFFC9949C521" box="[908,1035,1532,1558]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="215">V. limnense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is traced, a 
<typeStatus id="EC2F886E0111FF9BFB5DCFFC99A5C520" box="[1166,1255,1533,1559]" pageId="1" pageNumber="215">neotype</typeStatus>
based on a recent collection of the species is designated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
